  "description": "Mahendra Narayan Nidhi (24 February 1922 – 4 May 1999) was a Nepali politician, democracy fighter, and Gandhian leader. He was the Minister of water resources and local development in the Interim government after the 1990 Nepalese revolution, the General Secretary of the Nepali Congress, and the first deputy speaker of Pratinidhi Sabha of Nepal in 1959. He was elected twice to the parliament, in 1959 and 1991.",
